lua-copas
------------------------------------------
Copas is a dispatcher based on coroutines that can be used by TCP/IP 
servers. It uses LuaSocket as the interface with the TCP/IP stack.

A server registered with Copas should provide a handler for requests and 
use Copas socket functions to send the response. Copas loops through 
requests and invokes the corresponding handlers.

Runtime requirements:
  lua-5.1.3-1
  lua-socket-2.0.2-1

Build requirements:
  cygport-0.3.8-1
  make-3.81-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.keplerproject.org/copas/

Canonical download:
  http://luaforge.net/projects/copas/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack lua-copas-1.1.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./lua-copas-1.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lua-copas-1.1.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/lua-copas-1.1.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/share/doc/lua-copas-1.1.1/README
  /usr/share/doc/lua-copas-1.1.1/html/copas.png
  /usr/share/doc/lua-copas-1.1.1/html/index.html
  /usr/share/doc/lua-copas-1.1.1/html/license.html
  /usr/share/doc/lua-copas-1.1.1/html/manual.html
  /usr/share/doc/lua-copas-1.1.1/html/reference.html
  /usr/share/lua/5.1/copas.lua
  /usr/share/lua/5.1/copas/copas.lua

